{"questionId":"33364874","questionHtml":"<p>Find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>48</mn></math> &nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>48</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to solve their equation to find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)<br><br></strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> To award the <em><strong>M1</strong></em>, candidate’s equation must include <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></math>, and they must attempt to isolate <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math>.</p>\n<p><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>64</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn></math> (cm)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"33364874","referenceCode":"24N.1.SL.TZ2.2a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the value of r.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailabl